title: Passover Chopped Layered Salad
summary: Need a gluten free, dairy free, and vegetarian side dish? Passover Chopped Layered Salad could be an awesome recipe to try. One portion of this dish contains around 4g of protein, 5g of fat, and a total of 91 calories. This recipe serves 10. For 79 cents per serving, this recipe covers 14% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 1 person were glad they tried this recipe. If you have cucumber, vegetable broth, bell pepper, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 45 minutes. With a spoonacular score of 72%, this dish is good. Try Chopped & Layered Taco Salad, Chopped Salad with Roasted Chickpeas (My Favorite Chopped Salad), and Tex-Mex Chopped Salad for similar recipes.
instructions: To prepare the dressing, combine the first 8 ingredients, stirring with a whisk. Set aside.                                                                                                To prepare the salad, arrange the romaine in the bottom of a 2-quart glass bowl or trifle dish; top with iceberg. Layer radicchio, endive, cucumber, celery, carrot, bell pepper, tomato, red onion, and green onions evenly over lettuces. Drizzle with dressing. Cover and chill 4 hours or overnight.                                                                                                Arrange beets over green onions; top with eggs. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
